accessibility.text: Key themes and summary of issues
— Transparency as Remedy?
“Is it often done? Is it reported? QRP if not reported.”
“BUT, if you report that, is it still a QRP?”
IMG_2383.jpg

“the phrase \"questionable research practices” [should be reserved for] for unethical research practices such as falsifying data, dealing with participants in unethical ways, and mistreating animals. In fact, all of these should be labeled as bad research practices. Most of the \"gray area” of data analyses activities […] should be referred to as \"questionable reporting practices.”
Wigboldus, D. H. J., Dotsch, R. (2015) Encourage Playing with Data and Discourage Questionable Reporting Practices. Psychometrika. 81, 1–6.
“In fact, it is difficult to imagine any of the practices purported to be QRPs as questionable or ethically ambiguous if fully reported.
Woo, S. E., O'Boyle, E. H., Spector, P. E. (2017) Best practices in developing, conducting, and evaluating inductive research. Human Resource Management Review. 27, 255–264.
“OK if put in supplementary materials.”
